#. <section class="sutta" id="sn55.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.39:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Puññābhisandavagga"
msgstr "4. Overflowing Merit"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 39. Kāḷigodhasutta → kāligodhāsuttaṃ (bj) | kāḷi (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Kāḷigodhasutta"
msgstr "39. With Kāḷigodhā"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.39:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near "
"Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery."

#. VAR: kāḷigodhāya → kāligodhāya (bj)
msgctxt "sn55.39:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena "
"kāḷigodhāya sākiyāniyā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane "
"nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went "
"to the home of Kāḷigodhā the Sakyan lady, where he sat on the seat spread "
"out."

msgctxt "sn55.39:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kāḷigodhā sākiyānī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho kāḷigodhaṃ "
"sākiyāniṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Kāḷigodhā went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The "
"Buddha said to her:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.397"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.39:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Catūhi kho, godhe, dhammehi samannāgatā ariyasāvikā sotāpannā hoti "
"avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā."
msgstr ""
"“Godhā, a female noble disciple who has four things is a stream-enterer, not "
"liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening."

msgctxt "sn55.39:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn55.39:2.3"
msgid "Idha, godhe, ariyasāvikā buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgatā hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.39:2.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.39:2.5"
msgid "Dhamme … pe …"
msgstr "the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.39:2.6"
msgid "saṃghe … pe …"
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

#. VAR: payatapāṇinī → payatapāṇī (bj, s1, s2, pts1) | payatapāṇi (s3)
msgctxt "sn55.39:2.7"
msgid ""
"vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgā payatapāṇinī "
"vossaggaratā yācayogā dānasaṃvibhāgaratā."
msgstr ""
"And they live at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-"
"handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share."

msgctxt "sn55.39:2.8"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, godhe, catūhi dhammehi samannāgatā ariyasāvikā sotāpannā hoti "
"avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A female noble disciple who has these four things is a stream-enterer, not "
"liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.39:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Yānimāni, bhante, bhagavatā cattāri sotāpattiyaṅgāni desitāni, saṃvijjante "
"dhammā mayi, ahañca tesu dhammesu sandissāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, these four factors of stream-entry that were taught by the Buddha are "
"found in me, and I am seen in them."

msgctxt "sn55.39:3.2"
msgid "Ahañhi, bhante, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgatā—"
msgstr "For I have experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.39:3.3"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.39:3.4"
msgid "Dhamme … pe …"
msgstr "the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.39:3.5"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …"
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "sn55.39:3.6"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kho pana kiñci kule deyyadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ appaṭivibhattaṃ sīlavantehi "
"kalyāṇadhammehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And I share without reservation all the gifts available to give in our "
"family with those who are ethical and of good character.”"

msgctxt "sn55.39:3.7"
msgid "“Lābhā te, godhe, suladdhaṃ te, godhe."
msgstr "“You’re fortunate, Godhā, so very fortunate,"

msgctxt "sn55.39:3.8"
msgid "Sotāpattiphalaṃ tayā, godhe, byākatan”ti."
msgstr "You have declared the fruit of stream-entry.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.39:3.9"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
